cs.CV, cs.IR, cs.MM, cs.LG, cs.HC. 

The paper deals with image processing and computer vision techniques for gender recognition and biometric identification using a large dataset of hand images. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also involves machine learning techniques, which could fall under cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.IR (Information Retrieval). The use of convolutional neural networks (CNNs) and support vector machine classifiers suggests that the paper could also belong to cs.MM (Multimedia) and the focus on human-computer interaction could place it under cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction).
